The People of the State of Illinois, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Bookert T. Walls, Defendant-Appellant.(No. 58486;First District (5th Division)April 11, 1974.

BARRETT, J., took no part.

James J. Doherty, Public Defender, of Chicago (Daniel Miranda, Assistant Public Defender, of counsel), for appellant.Bernard Carey, State’s Attorney, of Chicago (Patrick T. Driscoll, Jr., and Dorothy B. Johnson, Assistant State’s Attorneys, of counsel), for the People. PER CURIAM.
